node.text: How do I properly thank you all? I’m speechless...my sister surprised me with this montage of videos from all of you!! How did you all pull this surprise???? Today was the most special birthday celebration because of all of you and also my amazing family! I’m truly blessed beyond words. I’ll forever remember today! Thank you so so so much!!!

node.text: Let’s have a heart to heart… if you were in my stories, you saw some pretty mean messages that were sent to me that I shared yesterday night. The reality is, it’s not the first time, and it’s a reality I deal with constantly from people who feel the need to judge or comment on my physical appearance. Get a nose job, get lip fillers, Botox, put makeup up on, fix your face… you name it, I’ve received it. To take it further, my kids were thrown in the mix. Will I change who I am because of it? No. Will I run and change my appearance! No. Because It took me years but I have come to love me. All of me. The perfect and the imperfects. And I am damn proud of it. Do I block those people? You bet! 😀So today’s post is a gentle reminder to please be compassionate, please be kind… you never know what people are going through. Be the light in someone’s life, be the reason for their smile, sprinkle love and joy rather than hate. Inspire kindness, no matter how small the gesture. The world we live in right now has become filled with heavy news and sad realities for many, but we are able to control our own actions and be the rainbow others need. Better yet, it’s a simple as this: speak to others the way you’d want to be spoken to. Treat others the way you’d want to be treated. Today and every day, I want to send lots of love and light to each one of you and may your evening be filled with peace and joy. Love you all ❤️

node.text: This weekend was Celine’s Sweet 16 party. We have been planning it for over a month and she got to invite some friends to celebrate with. I wanted her to be involved in the planning, so we worked together to narrow down the color scheme and look for her party. You can swipe and see all the details! I honestly wouldn’t have been able to make it all happen without some amazingly talented vendors who helped make it all so special! @mklrworld did Celine’s balloon arch and “Celine’s Sweet 16” wall, the number 16 with balloons as well as the backdrop for the dessert table. She was so easy to coordinate with and did an amazing job with all the details! @flourhousecakes made the cake for Celine. And can I just say how blown away we were with the reveal! He exceeded my expectation and created a masterpiece! I honestly did not want to cut that cake 🤪. @whyimagine.mi set up the food table and dessert table! She’s so creative and set up the beautiful personalized food table and dessert table! She also personalized the goodie boxes! She worked closely with @sweettreat_by_sanaa_and_juliet who made all the beautiful dessert for the table! Did you see all that prettiness? Although @_imadination couldn’t be as involved with the planning because she was getting married and on her honey moon ( congratulations Medina!) she went out of her way to help out in any way she could to help pull this all together for me. I set up and decorated the dining table for Celine and her friends to hang out and eat from.
